<ab><lb n="0"/>  <gap reason="lost" unit="line" quantity="1"/>  <lb n="1"/> <w>speculator </w> <w><expan><abbr>legion</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan></w> <num value="3">III</num> <placeName>Gallicae</placeName></ab>
</div>
         <div type="apparatus">
            <p>MAMA printed an initial <foreign xml:lang="la">L</foreign> above the opening letter. This is presumably an interpretation of a mark just above the surviving ram's head, on the left; there is nothing on the stone immediately above the surviving line.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               <gap reason="lost" unit="line" quantity="1"/> Scout of the third legion Gallicae.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The rather naive style of the relief suggests the same time-period as the lettering (so Natalie de Chaisemartin).</p>
         </div>
